{"questionId":"14838791","questionHtml":"<p>Show that lines&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math> intersect at a point&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math> and find the position vector of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>attempt to set at least two components of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>M</mi></math> equal&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> &nbsp;M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>1</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>s</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mi>t</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>3</mn><mi>s</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>t</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>s</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi></math></p>\n<p>attempt to solve two of their equations simultaneously&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp;(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;OR&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>&nbsp; A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>substitute<strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>s</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn></math>&nbsp;</strong>and<strong>&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp;</strong>into&nbsp;remaining component e.g.&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>6</mn><mfenced><mn>2</mn></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>=</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>11</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>+</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>2</mn><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>recognition that 2<sup>nd</sup> and 3<sup>rd</sup> equations are equivalent&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong> R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>position vector of A is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mtable><mtr><mtd><mn>5</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>8</mn></mtd></mtr><mtr><mtd><mn>9</mn></mtd></mtr></mtable></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept a row vector and/or coordinates.</p>\n<p>The final <em><strong>A1</strong></em> is independent of <em><strong>R1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[5 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14838791","referenceCode":"23N.2.AHL.TZ1.12a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that lines L and M intersect at a point A and find the position vector of A.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 5]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.12—Vector definitions","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.14—Vector equation of line","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.15—Classification of lines","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.17—Vector equations of a plane","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.18—Intersections of lines & planes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}